The paper focuses on evaluating the effectiveness of different syntactic CCG parsers for a semantic slot-filling task, which falls under the domain of natural language processing (NLP) and computational linguistics (CL). Therefore, cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also involves machine learning techniques for unsupervised grammar induction, which falls under the domains of artificial intelligence (AI) and machine learning (LG). Hence, cs.AI and cs.LG are also likely sub-categories. The paper also involves evaluating the performance of the parsers on a new dataset, which falls under the domain of information retrieval (IR). Therefore, cs.IR is another likely sub-category. Finally, the paper involves evaluating the semantic parsing models on a task-based evaluation, which involves neural networks and optimization techniques, which falls under the domain of neural networks (NE). Hence, cs.NE is another likely sub-category.
